      <p>The Apple of My Eye</p>
      <p>We kept it cool. We kept it dry,</p>
      <p>We did not want our friends to pry,</p>
      <p>For I was only seventeen, and she,</p>
      <p>The apple of my eye.</p>

      <p>We made no plans, and if we met,</p>
      <p>We’d touch, and gently touch, not grope,</p>
      <p>For she came from another world,</p>
      <p>And I was full of love and hope.</p>

      <p>Through shafts of light, to muffled drums,</p>
      <p>We swore we’d leave it all to chance.</p>
      <p>Let’s face the future, as it comes!</p>
      <p>And so began our lifelong dance.</p>

      <p>We had no doubt, we had no fear,</p>
      <p>We did not play it by the rule,</p>
      <p>For she was on her grand career,</p>
      <p>And I stood firm (though still at school).</p>

      <p>Living alone in a house,</p>
      <p>Waiting for no-one to come,</p>
      <p>Where are they now?</p>
      <p>Kisses that fastened my heart and stopped my mouth</p>
      <p>Dumb.</p>
